annotation.TEXT: Pop quiz: See that Notepad filename at the top of the screen here? What game is that quote from? First to give me the correct answer gets 5 Happy Smile Points! (Note: The quote doesn't include ".txt - Notepad", obviously.) (UPDATE: UltraLeet31337 and Photon Error Gaming both got it. It's Rockin' Kats for the NES.)
Whoa, be careful not to get knocked off by stomping an enemy!
I guess I'm gonna need a T-switch here.
Yep, so that's another way to deal with them. However, I really shouldn't waste time here, because I didn't see any reset doors, and failing to get past those munchers in time would not be good.
Outta my way! (I really should've spin jumped on that bugger.)
Ah, what? I have to keep using this slow thing? I really don't have much time here!
There's a silver T-switch, and there's an obvious reason to use it.
Goal tape average so far: 80 / 2 = 40 stars each.
Whoa! How did I not collide with that Rex there?
Demo count: 3
Uhh... There's a solid invisible block above the right side of this mushroom here. Umm... Why?
There's a shell that's obviously meant for that ? block...
To be continued...
Demo count: 4
BGM: Super Mario 64 - Wing/Vanish Cap
Yeah, there's a springboard hidden behind this bush here. I'm usually good at finding hidden things like that much sooner. Oh, well. At least I did eventually find it.
Tush!
So, the secret path it is, and it's... the White Switch Palace, eh? Interesting...

2-life combo! Now, I know I didn't hit the Banzai Bill the previous time, but what was the other enemy I missed before? (Looking back, it was a blue koopa at the very beginning of the spiky corridor that must've despawned the first time.)
So, I didn't see any dotted white outlines in the previous levels...
Oh, there's a door. I wonder if it's a reset door...
Alright, let's go explore Happy Goomba Hills! It's so happy that it's got two exits for me to find!
Whoa! Get outta the way, Paragoomba!
I'm surprised I wasn't given this tip in the first level, which definitely necessitated the ability to run up walls.
Once again, the starting camera angle was a little high there.
The message is unchanged, although it has a blue border for some reason. That's perfectly fine, though.
Oh, this is a kind of neat use of layer 2. Also, that's a neat background!
And, all of a sudden, timed lift trickiness. Also, my time's running out.
Move faster, diagonal platform!
Oops, I despawned the shell. Well, I may as well see if that's a reset door...
Oh, come on. Is there just one more enemy around here so that I can get a 1-up? ...Nuts.
Ah, and there's the key, which was actually visible from below, but I was too busy racing through while invincible to notice.
Whoa, that was weird. I ran up through the mushroom platform there, but at least I didn't collide with the Chuck.
Nope. Nuts.
Shut up, clock!
Demo count: 5
It's obvious that I'll need to get up to where that Banzai Bill is shooting from, but I can't run up that wall, and there are no hidden blocks there... Did I miss something?

Oh, great. Now there's a YouTube logo in the lower-right corner of the video in the annotation editor that says "Watch on YouTube.com" when I hover the mouse over it. Really, Google?! That's unnecessary, and will only get in the way!
Wow, you can't spin jump on it, and it's instant death?! I thought it was just gonna be a Spiny equivalent, since it can be killed by a thrown Goomba.
Oh, this mushroom is not merely background. You can stand on it.
Farfignewton! Man, this hack seems to have a problem with enemies at the tops of walls that I'm running up...
Tush!
I'm definitely not gonna try squeezing myself under that pipe, because I know that'll kill me.
BGM: Legend of Zelda: Majora's Mask - Stone Tower Temple
Okay, there's the goal, but is there anything hidden up here?
And the secret exit has been unlocked! Now, which way will I go next? Let's find out!
Oh, this is neat. While I'm standing on this platform, I can control it. However, it's kind of slow...
Too bad the scoring doesn't work, so any combos that don't garner 1-ups are pointless.
Oh, I see that Yoshi head over there!

Yeah, I forget where I learned this (probably a Kaizo-like hack), but running up a wall made of munchers does not hurt you. (However, if the very top of such a wall is a muncher, you have to jump with perfect timing to not get bitten.)
So, what did hitting the white ! switch do? And what is this "Chilly Shroom" that's mentioned in the title of the next level? Find out next time!
BGM: Adventures of Lolo 3 - Action Puzzle Room
Okay, I've found it. It wasn't exactly ultra-obvious, but it's something that I really should've checked earlier.
Does hitting the white ! switch let me open the white fridge in here?

Yes, I can see that there's something to the upper-left, and it might be the secret exit. However, I think I'll do the normal exit first here (unless it turns out the secret exit is further ahead and I find it by chance).
That unlocks The Chilly Shroom. However, there's still a secret exit to get from Happy Goomba Hills, of course!
Nope! So, I've gotta completely avoid contact!
Oh, what? Don't tell me that I had to race all the way here during that T-switch's effect-- Oh, wait! I just remembered that it's okay to run up muncher walls!
Sorry, I couldn't find any nice-looking pictures representing the downfall of Satan.
I wonder if that silver coin was another evil death mushroom... Or it could've been a Wiggler I guess.
Oh, there's another reset door. Well, I would assume it's a reset door.
Just a way to almost get myself killed! Why is that alcove and log platform even there?
Well, it still gives me invincibility, and it looks like it's needed to get through this spike-filled corridor up here!
Zwee! That's an unusual way to place a midpoint. Also, I assume the pipe above it is the midpoint entrance.
Can it be slide-killed? I gotta know.
That's odd. Why couldn't I run up that wall? Was that just an ordinary 45° slope and not a wall triangle?
Hello, and welcome back to some hat searching. Can I destroy this table with a spin jump now that I'm big? ...No? What about the fridge?
"Marios" needs apostrophe badly.
I'm gonna need a shell or Goomba or something to hit that ? block.
Made it that time.
I also see those spikes down there.
Tush!
...Nope. Aww... Oh, well.
There's another one of those things. It almost looks like a poison mushroom.
Ooh, a star-- Wait, what the heck? That's an odd-looking star!
Go, my white blocks, and fill the world with your whiteness!
Okay, so... Umm... How exactly do I proceed here?
Yep, just barely, and I got a 40, which is fine.
Hmm... Now I think it wants me to put the springboard in the little hole there, but I don't feel like it.
Can the evil death mushroom be transformed by the silver T-switch?

This would seem like a major level design flaw here, but if that were the case, it would be ultra-obvious that the level is unwinnable (unless the player performs a wall jump). So, I must've missed something ultra-obvious. Gimme a moment here.
I don't know what I'm trying to do here, honestly.
There it is! Also, there's an off screen ceiling in case I get any ideas about breaking the level.
Well, there's the keyhole, and I'm going to assume that the path to the upper-left of that other place leads to the key.
And down here is the last Yoshi head. Well, I can definitely clear the level in time, but is there enough time to try for a high number of stars?
D'oh! Umm... I just realized that I haven't seen a single power up in this level. I think the only way to power up would be from midpoint if I'm small.
Tush!

Whoa, that was an rather high starting camera position. Neidave, you might want to adjust that. But yes, that was indeed a reset door, which makes me wonder why I didn't see a reset door in the first section.
Bah. I wasted too much time checking if there was anything to the left of the key. Well, at least there's a reset door here!
! switch jump!
Tush!
Whoa, what was that thing that I just killed?
Whoa. Possible level design flaw there. I have not seen any reset door or pipe, so if I failed to get through that last pair of coins in time, I would've been trapped!
Whoa, watch out for falling Goombas. Also, gotta be patient to get this Yoshi head.
BGM: Super Mario Galaxy - Honeyhive Galaxy
